{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 1704963, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Eillesthis", "body": "[npc=53286]'s family in the memory unlocked from the [item=69855] while visiting his [object=208790] on [quest=29303]:\r\nThis particular Arch Druid Fandral Staghelm, father\r\n[npc=53289], wife\r\n[npc=53291], daughter\r\n[quote]\r\nArch Druid Fandral Staghelm says: Time passes, yet the sting of his death will not fade.\r\nLeyara says: Valstann, my dear husband, you left us too soon.\r\nLeyara says: Our child has been born. It's a girl! A beautiful baby girl.\r\nLeyara says: I named her Istaria. She has your eyes.\r\nArch Druid Fandral Staghelm says: Leyara, the two of you are all I have left. I swear to you, on my life, you and my granddaughter will ALWAYS have my protection.\r\n[/quote]", "date": "2012-08-27T14:50:48-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 1101858, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "noobstar2112", "body": "SPOILER ALERT\r\n\r\nIn the book: Warcraft:Stormrage, Fandral gets corrpupted by Xavius, The Nightmare Lord. He is tricked to beleive his son was still alive. His son's image was actually a demon.", "date": "2010-08-16T13:22:16-05:00", "rating": 27, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "It would be nice if they explained why he's there. When I did the quest, I got down there and was like you look familar...then it clicked. They didn't exactly say anything on the quest about it. Unless I missed something... (wouldn't doubt it if I did)", "creationdate": "2010-12-27T06:36:14-06:00", "id": 208644, "rating": 11, "commentid": 1101858, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "341073", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It's how they get you to read the books. =P", "creationdate": "2011-01-08T03:03:30-06:00", "id": 213037, "rating": 10, "commentid": 1101858, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Coobra", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "At least we get to get revenge on him in the Firelands.", "creationdate": "2011-04-29T10:22:31-05:00", "id": 240571, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1101858, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "491046", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "That book is terrible too; slogging through it was PAINFUL and I say this as someone who used to read a lot of RL Stine.", "creationdate": "2012-04-01T22:00:37-05:00", "id": 532357, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1101858, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MiltiadesBooga", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": fa